Reasoning: The paper investigates the importance of social links in the propagation of information in online social networks, specifically the social news aggregator Digg.com. This topic falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which falls under the sub-category of digital libraries (cs.DL). Finally, the paper discusses the topological properties of the network, which falls under the sub-category of social informatics (cs.SI).
